    <p align="center" style="text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Unanticipated Closure Press Release- SFSP Meal Service</span></span></span></span></p>

<p align="center" style="text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>March 17, 2020</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"> </p>

<p align="center" style="text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Southeast Valley Schools</span></span></span></span></p>

<p align="center" style="text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Southeast Webster-Grand and Prairie Valley Community School Districts </span></span></span></span></p>

<p align="center" style="text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>to Serve Meals to Children During School Closure</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"> </p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The closures to the Southeast Valley Schools which include Southeast Webster-Grand and Prairie Valley Community School Districts due to the COVID-19 virus could be especially tough for families who receive free and reduced-price meals at school.  It could mean hunger for many students.  To help fight the hunger, the Southeast Valley School is teaming with the Summer Food Service Program to provide free meals during the school closure.  </span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>All children ages 0-18 are eligible for free meals at open sites through this program. <span style="color:black">The meals are available to all children, regardless of whether they qualify for free or reduced-price lunch during the school year. </span> Southeast Valley Schools will be providing meals at Dayton Elementary School in Dayton and Southeast Valley High School in Gowrie.</span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:12.0pt; margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:12.0pt; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="background:white"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="color:black">Last week, the Secretary of Agriculture, Sonny Perdue announced proactive flexibilities to allow meal service during school closures to minimize potential exposure to the coronavirus. During an unexpected school closure, schools can leverage their participation in one of USDA’s summer meal programs to provide meals at no cost to students. Under normal circumstances, those meals must be served in a group setting. However, in a public health emergency, the law allows USDA the authority to waive the group setting meal requirement, which is vital during a social distancing situation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:12.0pt; margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:12.0pt; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="background:white"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="color:black">These flexibilities have made it possible for school districts who may not otherwise qualify for the program to provide meals through the Summer Food Service Program during unanticipated closures due to COVID-19.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-top:12.0pt; margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:12.0pt; margin-left:0in"> </p>

<p style="margin-top:12.0pt; margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:12.0pt; margin-left:0in"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="background:white"><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><span style="font-size:11.0pt"><span style="color:black">Contact the school central office in Gowrie at 515-352-3173 regarding any questions for this service while school is closed.</span></span></span></span></span></p>

   
       
